Japan consumes a quarter of the world's tuna, facing criticism from environmentalists for driving the species to near extinction.
An international commission reduced the Mediterranean bluefin tuna catch, leading to import shortages in Japan.
Conservation bodies demand a moratorium on large tuna vessels to prevent further depletion.
The conference in Kobe aims to share information for sustainable tuna fishing.
Japan, a major consumer, seeks to lead in establishing a stable management system.
Efforts are underway to track tuna from sea to market to combat overfishing and preserve this valuable resource.
